{
  "id": "375a5910c101f05a",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/monad.foundation/6366a8f2-34ca-426a-a456-c5f6fed91c80/application",
    "company": "Monad Foundation",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "375a5910c101f05a",
    "department": "Business Development",
    "description": "The Monad Foundation is a team of dedicated ecosystem and community builders who are on a mission to massively grow the impact of decentralized tech. We believe that the Monad https://monad.xyz/ blockchain--the performant and parallel EVM Layer 1--will help decentralized apps eat the world.\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nMonad Foundation, a core contributor to the Monad protocol, is looking for a DeFi Specialist to serve as the operational backbone of DeFi growth across the Monad network. This is a hands-on, execution-heavy role for someone with encyclopedic knowledge of DeFi protocols, deep opinions on asset quality, and the coordination skills to onboard new protocols and assets from first conversation to live, liquid market.\n\nYou'll work directly with builders deploying on the Monad network, advising on protocol mechanics, identifying product gaps, and helping them ship better. You'll evaluate which assets are worth bringing to the ecosystem and which carry hidden risk. You'll coordinate across oracles, liquidators, DEX pools, curators, and bridges to make onboarding seamless. And you'll track the full state of DeFi on the Monad network in real time, spotting problems early and recommending where to allocate time or incentives for maximum impact.\n\nIf someone can hand you a protocol frontend you've never seen, and you can produce a sharp, actionable teardown in 30 minutes, this role is for you.\n\n\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Advise DeFi builders on the Monad network. You will provide succinct, hard-hitting feedback on protocol design, UX, market positioning, and competitive gaps. You should be able to open any Monad-native protocol's site and quickly produce an actionable list of strengths and weaknesses.\n\n - Execution-oriented. You will own end-to-end onboarding of new protocols and assets, coordinating across oracles, liquidators, DEX pool setup, curators, and bridging providers to bring new markets live.\n\n - Prioritization and research at the forefront. You will prioritize which assets to bring to the Monad network based on market demand, composability value, and rigorous risk assessment. You will research new assets and evaluate bridging mechanics, relative interest rates, liquidity depth, redemption windows, reserve transparency, and issuer controls.\n\n - Monitor the state of DeFi on the Monad network. You will flag gaps, imbalances, or inefficiencies. Recommend where to allocate time or incentive spend to address ecosystem-level problems.\n\n - Strategy mindset. You will inform incentive strategy with grounded opinions on what types of programs attract durable TVL per unit of spend versus what generates mercenary capital.\n\n - Grow DeFi on the Monad network. You will substantially grow the network as measured by TVL, volume, stablecoin market cap, RWA market cap, and fees generated.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\n - Encyclopedic DeFi knowledge. You can explain the value flow in any leading lending protocol (Aave, Morpho, Euler), walk through how a CDP, DEX, or yield-bearing stablecoin succeeds or fails, and articulate what each protocol category needs to get right to win.\n\n - Opinionated on asset quality. You track interest-bearing assets, stablecoins, and RWAs closely. You know the prevailing market opinion on key assets and can independently assess new ones for strengths and pitfalls.\n\n - Operationally rigorous. You can manage the full coordination chain of onboarding a new protocol or asset: oracles, liquidation infrastructure, DEX liquidity, curators, bridges. Nothing falls through the cracks.\n\n - Sharp protocol instincts. Given any DeFi protocol's frontend or documentation, you can rapidly identify what's working, what's broken, and what to fix. Your advice is specific, not generic.\n\n - Opinionated on incentive efficiency. You have a framework for evaluating which growth programs create flywheels versus which burn capital, and you can defend that framework with data and examples.\n\n - Strong communicator. You deliver concise, high-signal analysis and recommendations. Builders and internal stakeholders trust your judgment because your reasoning is transparent and well-supported.\n\n\nNICE TO HAVES\n\n - Strong knowledge of trading and markets; able to think in expected value (EV) terms and apply that lens to DeFi strategy.\n\n - Experience at a DeFi protocol in a growth, strategy, or protocol operations capacity.\n\n - Familiarity with the Monad network's architecture, performance characteristics, and ecosystem.\n\n - Comfort reading Solidity and understanding smart contract risk at a conceptual level.\n\n\nWHY WORK WITH US\n\n - Challenging problems. You’ll work on extremely challenging problems with massive impact.\n\n - Huge opportunity. The Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) standard is ubiquitous, but existing EVM-compatible chains are slow and bandwidth-constrained. Monad’s core innovations offer developers the best of both worlds (portability and performance) and are a game-changer for mass user adoption in crypto.\n\n - The right team. You’ll be part of an exceptional and highly-motivated team\n\n - Culture. We’re a lean team working together to achieve very ambitious goals. We are united in our culture of collaboration, low ego, and high-quality output. As an early member of our team, you’ll help continue to shape our culture.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
